[SN]TITLE[SN]
Peter Hickman to ride Smiths Racing BMW superbike at North West 200 in May

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Peter Hickman will compete at this year's North West 200 on the same Smiths Racing BMW Superbike which he will race in this season's British Superbike Championship.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Hickman, who became the North West 200's fastest ever newcomer in 2014, finished 2016 on a high by winning a second successive Macau Grand Prix.
"I know the BMW well having ridden it in the past," said the Englishman, 29.
"And we've been promised the right support from the factory in Germany."
Hickman clinched two British Superbike series wins in 2016 for the JG Speedfit Kawasaki team but his major international wins have been aboard a BMW.
