The Burton-on-Trent man took his first international road race win on one of the German manufacturer's bikes at the Ulster Grand Prix in 2015 and both his Macau victories have also been on a BMW.
After becoming the North West 200's fastest newcomer in 2014, Hickman missed the 2015 event because of injury but he claimed a Superstock runner-up spot and Supersport third place at last year's Triangle meeting.
In addition, Hickman also finished fourth in one of last year's Superbike races.
"As one of the fastest men on the roads today it will be great to have Peter back at the North West 200 in May," said North West Event Director Mervyn Whyte.
"The Smiths team has a superb racing pedigree having won races on the roads and short circuits and we are delighted the team will make their 2017 road racing debut with Peter at Portrush."
The North West 200 race week will start on 7 May with Saturday's main day of racing on 13 May.
